# Chainstats
This folder contains functions that calculate structure factors of random copolymers (2,3,and 4-point correlations).

Example 1: Two-point correlations of Gaussian random copolymer
`
clear;

N = 100;  % Number of Monomers
NM = 100; % Number of Kuhn steps per monomer
LAM = 0;  % Degree of chemical correlation
FA = 0.5; % Fraction of A-type monomers

kv = logspace(-4,2,50);
s2 = zeros(length(kv),2,2);
ssum = zeros(length(kv),1);  % SAA+SAB+SBA+SBB
for ii = 1:length(kv)
  k = kv(ii);  % wavevector
  s2(ii,:,:)=s2gc(N,NM,LAM,FA,k);
  ssum(ii) = sum(sum(s2(ii,:,:)))/power(N*NM,4);
end

figure;hold;
plot(kv,s2(:,1,1));  % Plots SAA for different k

% check normaliztion
figure;hold;
plot(kv,ssum);  % Plots SAA for different k
`